[49m[38;5;10m+       1[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Recipe 15.7: Python Implementation Example
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       2[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       3[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > **Heads up:** This is a deliberately simplified, illustrative implementation of the RL concepts from Recipe 15.7. It demonstrates the shape of a chronic disease treatment personalization system: patient environment modeling, multi-year state tracking, offline policy learning with batch-constrained Q-learning, safety constraint enforcement, and treatment recommendation generation. This is absolutely not production-ready. Chronic disease RL operates over months and years, requires extensive retrospective validation, prospective clinical trials, and likely FDA clearance before influencing any treatment decision. Consider this a learning tool for understanding how RL applies to long-horizon treatment optimization, not something you'd connect to a prescribing system.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       4[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       5[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       6[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       7[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Setup
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       8[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       9[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```bash
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      10[0m:[38;5;10m[49m pip install boto3 numpy
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      11[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      12[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      13[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Your environment needs AWS credentials configured (via environment variables, instance profile, or `~/.aws/credentials`). The IAM role or user needs `sagemaker:InvokeEndpoint`, `dynamodb:PutItem`, `dynamodb:GetItem`, `dynamodb:Query`, `s3:GetObject`, `s3:PutObject`, and `cloudwatch:PutMetricData`. You'll need a signed BAA because longitudinal treatment data is PHI regardless of de-identification status.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      14[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      15[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      16[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      17[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Config and Constants
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      18[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      19[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Before the logic, here's the configuration that defines the chronic disease treatment MDP. These constants encode clinical knowledge about type 2 diabetes management: what outcomes matter, how to score them, what treatment transitions are safe, and what the action space looks like. In a real system, these would be developed with endocrinologists, validated against clinical practice guidelines (ADA Standards of Care), and reviewed by your institution's pharmacy committee.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      20[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      21[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      22[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import json
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      23[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import time
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      24[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import uuid
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      25[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import logging
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      26[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from decimal import Decimal
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      27[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from typing import Dict, List, Optional, Tuple
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      28[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      29[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import boto3
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      30[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import numpy as np
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      31[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from botocore.config import Config
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      32[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      33[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Structured logging. Never log patient identifiers or PHI values.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      34[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      35[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger.setLevel(logging.INFO)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      36[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      37[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Retry config for AWS calls.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      38[0m:[38;5;10m[49m BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG = Config(retries={"max_attempts": 3, "mode": "adaptive"})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      39[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      40[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # =============================================================================
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      41[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # CLINICAL DOMAIN: TYPE 2 DIABETES MANAGEMENT
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      42[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # =============================================================================
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      43[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # This example focuses on type 2 diabetes because it has:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      44[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # - Clear outcome metrics (HbA1c, hypoglycemia events)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      45[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # - Well-defined treatment escalation pathways
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      46[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # - Multi-year time horizons where personalization matters
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      47[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # - Enough clinical trial data to validate against
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      48[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      49[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # --- Outcome Targets ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      50[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # HbA1c is the primary outcome: a 3-month average of blood glucose control.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      51[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # The ADA recommends < 7% for most adults, but individualized targets matter.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      52[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Older patients or those with comorbidities may have relaxed targets (< 8%).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      53[0m:[38;5;10m[49m HBA1C_TARGET = 7.0          # % : standard target for most adults
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      54[0m:[38;5;10m[49m HBA1C_RELAXED_TARGET = 8.0  # % : relaxed target for frail/elderly/comorbid
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      55[0m:[38;5;10m[49m HBA1C_DANGEROUS_LOW = 5.5   # % : below this suggests over-treatment risk
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      56[0m:[38;5;10m[49m HBA1C_DANGEROUS_HIGH = 10.0 # % : above this risks microvascular complications
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      57[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      58[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # --- Decision Interval ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      59[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Unlike ICU settings (hours), chronic disease decisions happen quarterly.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      60[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # HbA1c reflects ~3 months of glucose control, so treatment changes need
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      61[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # at least 3 months to show effect. Changing faster causes oscillation.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      62[0m:[38;5;10m[49m DECISION_INTERVAL_MONTHS = 3
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      63[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      64[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # --- Action Space ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      65[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Treatment actions for type 2 diabetes, ordered by escalation level.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      66[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Each action represents a treatment regimen, not a single drug.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      67[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # The agent picks one of these at each quarterly decision point.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      68[0m:[38;5;10m[49m TREATMENT_ACTIONS = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      69[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     {"id": 0, "name": "lifestyle_only",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      70[0m:[38;5;10m[49m      "desc": "Diet, exercise, weight management. No medications."},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      71[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     {"id": 1, "name": "metformin_monotherapy",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      72[0m:[38;5;10m[49m      "desc": "First-line oral: metformin 500-2000mg daily."},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      73[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     {"id": 2, "name": "metformin_plus_sglt2",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      74[0m:[38;5;10m[49m      "desc": "Dual oral: metformin + SGLT2 inhibitor (empagliflozin, dapagliflozin)."},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      75[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     {"id": 3, "name": "metformin_plus_glp1",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      76[0m:[38;5;10m[49m      "desc": "Metformin + GLP-1 receptor agonist (semaglutide, liraglutide)."},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      77[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     {"id": 4, "name": "metformin_plus_dpp4",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      78[0m:[38;5;10m[49m      "desc": "Metformin + DPP-4 inhibitor (sitagliptin). Less potent but well-tolerated."},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      79[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     {"id": 5, "name": "triple_oral",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      80[0m:[38;5;10m[49m      "desc": "Metformin + SGLT2 + DPP-4. Maximum oral therapy before injectables."},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      81[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     {"id": 6, "name": "metformin_plus_basal_insulin",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      82[0m:[38;5;10m[49m      "desc": "Oral + basal insulin (glargine, degludec). Major escalation step."},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      83[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     {"id": 7, "name": "intensive_insulin",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      84[0m:[38;5;10m[49m      "desc": "Basal-bolus insulin regimen. Maximum pharmacological intervention."},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      85[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      86[0m:[38;5;10m[49m NUM_ACTIONS = len(TREATMENT_ACTIONS)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      87[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      88[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # --- State Features ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      89[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # The state captures everything relevant to a treatment decision.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      90[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Chronic disease RL has a much richer patient context than acute care
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      91[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # because you have years of history and lifestyle factors matter enormously.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      92[0m:[38;5;10m[49m STATE_FEATURES = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      93[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Primary outcome and trend
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      94[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     {"name": "hba1c_current", "min": 4.0, "max": 14.0,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      95[0m:[38;5;10m[49m      "why": "Current HbA1c: the primary metric driving treatment decisions"},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      96[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     {"name": "hba1c_prev_quarter", "min": 4.0, "max": 14.0,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      97[0m:[38;5;10m[49m      "why": "Previous quarter's HbA1c for trend detection"},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      98[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     {"name": "hba1c_trend", "min": -2.0, "max": 2.0,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      99[0m:[38;5;10m[49m      "why": "Rate of change per quarter; negative means improving"},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     100[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Hypoglycemia burden
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     101[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     {"name": "hypo_events_quarter", "min": 0, "max": 20,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     102[0m:[38;5;10m[49m      "why": "Number of hypoglycemic episodes in past quarter"},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     103[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     {"name": "severe_hypo_ever", "min": 0, "max": 1,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     104[0m:[38;5;10m[49m      "why": "Binary: ever had severe hypoglycemia requiring assistance"},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     105[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Current treatment
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     106[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     {"name": "current_treatment_level", "min": 0, "max": 7,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     107[0m:[38;5;10m[49m      "why": "Current treatment action index (for transition constraints)"},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     108[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     {"name": "months_on_current_treatment", "min": 0, "max": 60,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     109[0m:[38;5;10m[49m      "why": "Duration on current regimen; short duration means give it more time"},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     110[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Patient factors
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     111[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     {"name": "age", "min": 18, "max": 95,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     112[0m:[38;5;10m[49m      "why": "Older patients get relaxed targets and avoid hypoglycemia risk"},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     113[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     {"name": "bmi", "min": 18, "max": 55,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     114[0m:[38;5;10m[49m      "why": "Obesity affects drug choice (GLP-1 agonists help with weight)"},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     115[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     {"name": "egfr", "min": 10, "max": 120,
